00:03:18.610 --> 00:03:22.370
I want to start with just
thinking about visual literacy,

00:03:22.370 --> 00:03:27.460
and what visual literacy is,
especially what it includes.

00:03:27.460 --> 00:03:33.150 position:66%
Basically, I like to remember that when
we think about visual literacy strategies,

00:03:33.150 --> 00:03:40.280 position:59%
I think about Bloom's Taxonomy, and it
includes all of the levels of blooms.

00:03:40.280 --> 00:03:46.820 position:59%
And, visual literacy products include,
but are not limited to; photographs,

00:03:46.820 --> 00:03:50.510
illustrations, maps, diagrams, ads.

00:03:50.510 --> 00:03:54.330
The works of art can be two
dimensional and three dimensional.

00:03:54.330 --> 00:03:58.260 position:72%
They can be moving, and it can be still media.

00:03:58.260 --> 00:04:06.670 position:73%
And, a very visually literate learner will take
in to consideration things like the context,

00:04:06.670 --> 00:04:12.060
the culture, ethics, aesthetics,
and technical components.

00:04:12.060 --> 00:04:15.370 position:67%
&gt;&gt; I asked my pre-service teachers how many

00:04:15.370 --> 00:04:18.750
of them could read music, and
several raised their hands.

00:04:18.750 --> 00:04:23.840 position:73%
We discussed how the word read is used here,
and in other ways when we use the word reading.

00:04:23.840 --> 00:04:26.280
Reading a knitting a pattern,
reading graphs, or charts,

00:04:26.280 --> 00:04:32.570 position:70%
and how reading in these cases doesn't mean
text, but it definitely refers to a literacy.

00:04:32.570 --> 00:04:37.600 position:67%
So, when asking our students to analyze
images, we have to guide them in developing

00:04:37.600 --> 00:04:42.210
that visual literacy just like
we would in textual literacy.

00:04:42.210 --> 00:04:50.810 position:64%
&gt;&gt; So, what we're going to share with you
